    <stitle>SPRING ASSEMBLIES AND SHOCK ABSORBERS - SHOCK ABSORBERS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>SHOCK ABSORBERS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <para>Shock absorbers control vehicle body sway, and also eliminate excessive tire wear, front wheel shimmy
                and spring breakage. They improve the ride qualities, and are especially effective when the vehicle is
                empty or only partly loaded.
            </para>
            <para>The direct-acting type shock absorber has sealed construction and requires no periodic maintenance (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0300406">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0300406" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300406" filename="../figg03/g0300406.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="152px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Direct-Acting Shock Absorber</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
